data.title: Kylie Minogue (Pop Star and Singer)
data.meta_description: The Australian singer and actress came to fame playing the role of Charlene in Australian soap "Neighbours" opposite love interest Jason Donovan,...
data.text:
Profession: Pop Star and Singer

Biography: The Australian singer and actress came to fame playing the role of Charlene in Australian soap "Neighbours" opposite love interest Jason Donovan, but went on to become an international singing star.

Some of her most famous songs include "Can't Get You Out of My Head", "Spinning Around" and "I Should Be so Lucky".

Her singing career began working with the British pop outfit Stock, Aitken & Waterman before developing a more mature image with later albums. Minogue has mostly stayed loyal to her disco-inspired sound and is known for her stage shows, sexy image and large gay fanbase.

Born: May 28, 1968

Birthplace: Melbourne, Victoria, Australia

Age: 56 years old
